Class IteratorWorker<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>

java.lang.Object
  edu.uci.ics.luci.lucicabinet.IteratorWorker<K,V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public abstract class IteratorWorker<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This is a class that is used by luci-cabinet to iterate over synchronized sets.

One uses it by passing the IteratorWorker class to a LUCICabinetMap. The LUCICabinetMap, instantiates the class, iterates overs it's members and executes the IteratorWorker's methods in turn: initialize iterate combine shutdown

It should be subclassed and the appropriate methods overridden.

Although there will be no changes made to the database between initialization and through the end of the iterate method, there may be changes to the underlying database after the completion of iterate and the call to shutdown.

Because a particular call to LUCICabinetMap.iterate be used in concurrent contexts, it is important that any state that is maintained internally in IteratorWorker is maintained in concurrent-safe data-structures (so that simultaneous calls to iterate don't cause problems). Likewise because IteratorWorker might be sent across the network to work on portions of the database at a time, the combine function needs to take any state in the IteratorWorker that is passed and incorporate it into its own state.

Method Detail

initialize

protected void initialize(LUCICabinetMap<K,V> parent,
                          IteratorWorkerConfig iwc)
The initialize method is called once before iteration. It is passed a reference to the database that is being iterated over. It may write to the parent database.

Parameters:
parent -
iwc - A class containing configuration parameters.

iterate

protected abstract boolean iterate(K key,
                                   V value)
The iterate function is called once for every element in the database. It may not write to the database. If it tries to, then it will lock indefinitely.

If this function returns true then iteration will attempt to stop at some undefined point in the future. It is a request to stop for efficiency, not a guarantee of stoppage.

Parameters:
key - The key currently being iterated over.
value - The associated value for the key
Returns:
true if the iteration should stop, false if the iteration should continue

combine

protected abstract void combine(IteratorWorker<K,V> iw)
The combine method is called to join separate iterations over portions of the whole database. It needs to take any state from the iw parameter passed and incorporate it into itself.

Parameters:
iw -

shutdown

protected void shutdown(LUCICabinetMap<K,V> parent)
The shutdown method is called once at the end of the iteration. It is passed a reference to the database that was just iterated over. It may write to the parent database.

Parameters:
parent -
